1 olive oil
1 parsnip
½ Brown Onion
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 packet chicken thigh
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet creamy pesto dressing
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut parsnip into bite-sized chunks. Slice onion (see ingredients)
into wedges.
• Divide peeled pumpkin pieces, parsnip and onion over two lined oven
trays. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast veggies until golden and tender,
25-30 minutes.

• Meanwhile, combine Aussie spice blend, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch
of pepper in a large bowl. Add chicken thigh and turn to coat.
• When the veggies have 20 minutes cook time remaining, add chicken to
the side of an oven tray.
• Return to the oven and bake until chicken is cooked through,
18-22 minutes.

TIP: Watch the veggies closely to ensure they don't overcook!

• When the veggies are done, add baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of white
wine vinegar and olive oil to the oven trays. Gently toss to combine. Season
to taste.

• Slice spiced chicken.
• Divide roasted pumpkin toss between plates. Top with chicken.
• Serve with creamy pesto dressing. Enjoy!